[2] Key updates
Date: Sun 12 Sep 2021
Source: Bloomberg News [edited]
https://blinks.bloomberg.com/news/stories/QZC37ODWX2PU


- Israel is making preparations to ensure it has sufficient vaccine supply in case a 4th round of COVID-19 shots is needed, the country's top health official said on [Sun 12 Sep 2021].

- President Joe Biden will announce his next steps to boost the global vaccine supply before this year's United Nations General Assembly begins, U.S. Surgeon General Vivek Murthy said. Republican governors said the vaccine mandates Biden announced last week will backfire and harden resistance to getting the shot.

- The U.K. will abandon plans to call for proof of vaccination to enter certain venues, and may soon drop mandatory testing for returning travelers as part of a further easing of coronavirus restrictions to be announced this week.

Key developments:
- Global Virus Tracker: Cases pass 224.5 million; deaths exceed 4.6 million
- Vaccine Tracker: More than 5.69 billion doses administered
- New York City schools reopen to a mixture of fear and relief
- Retired seniors in U.S. aren't covered by Biden's vaccine plan
- Alaska's top health official battens down for a difficult winter
- Reluctant firms now face mandate to require workers to be jabbed

Other news headlines:
