Communicated by:
ProMED
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Vaccination of the elderly, even with 82% of the elderly vaccinated in the US, seems important because of the severity of illness this demographic group experiences once infected. The importance of vaccination of the elderly is reinforced by their presence in nursing homes and hospitals, where virus spread can be rapid. - Mod.LK]

